.TH HYPEREXPORT 1 "January 2026" "hyperexport 1.0.0" "Hypervisor SDK"
.SH NAME
hyperexport \- interactive VM export CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hyperexport
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hyperexport
is an interactive command-line tool for exporting virtual machines from
VMware vSphere with a beautiful terminal UI. It provides VM discovery,
interactive selection, and real-time progress tracking.
.PP
The tool connects directly to vCenter/ESXi using the VMware Go SDK and
provides a modern, user-friendly interface with:
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
Automatic VM discovery
.IP \(bu 2
Interactive VM selection with search/filtering
.IP \(bu 2
Real-time progress bars and ETAs
.IP \(bu 2
Parallel download support
.IP \(bu 2
Resumable downloads with automatic retry
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version information and exit
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B hyperexport
uses the same configuration sources as
.BR hypervisord (1):
.RS 4
.IP 1. 3
Environment variables (highest priority)
.IP 2. 3
Configuration file
.IP 3. 3
Default values
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GOVC_URL
vCenter SDK URL (required)
.br
Example: https://vcenter.example.com/sdk
.TP
.B GOVC_USERNAME
vCenter username (required)
.br
Example: administrator@vsphere.local
.TP
.B GOVC_PASSWORD
vCenter password (required)
.TP
.B GOVC_INSECURE
Skip TLS verification (default: 0)
.br
Set to 1 for self-signed certificates
.TP
.B GOVC_DATACENTER
Default datacenter (optional)
.TP
.B DOWNLOAD_WORKERS
Number of parallel downloads (default: 4)
.TP
.B LOG_LEVEL
Logging level: debug, info, warn, error (default: info)
.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
When launched,
.B hyperexport
presents an interactive interface:
.PP
.B 1. Connection
.RS 4
Connects to vCenter and authenticates
.RE
.PP
.B 2. VM Discovery
.RS 4
Scans and lists all available VMs with animated spinner
.RE
.PP
.B 3. VM Selection
.RS 4
Interactive list with search/filter capabilities
.br
Use arrow keys to navigate, type to search, Enter to select
.RE
.PP
.B 4. Export Configuration
.RS 4
Choose output directory and export options
.RE
.PP
.B 5. Progress Tracking
.RS 4
Real-time progress bars for each disk
.br
Shows download speed, ETA, and completion percentage
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic Usage
.PP
Set credentials and run:
.RS 4
.nf
export GOVC_URL="https://vcenter.example.com/sdk"
export GOVC_USERNAME="admin@vsphere.local"
export GOVC_PASSWORD="secret"
export GOVC_INSECURE=1

hyperexport
.fi
.RE
.SS With Debug Logging
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
LOG_LEVEL=debug hyperexport
.fi
.RE
.SS Custom Worker Count
.PP
For faster downloads on high-bandwidth connections:
.RS 4
.nf
DOWNLOAD_WORKERS=8 hyperexport
.fi
.RE
.SH OUTPUT
Exports are saved in OVF format with the following structure:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
output_directory/
  vm-name/
    vm-name.ovf           # OVF descriptor
    vm-name.mf            # Manifest file
    disk-0.vmdk          # Virtual disks
    disk-1.vmdk
    ...
.fi
.RE
.SH FEATURES
.SS Beautiful Terminal UI
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
Color-coded status indicators
.IP \(bu 2
Animated spinners and progress bars
.IP \(bu 2
Formatted tables with VM details
.IP \(bu 2
Real-time statistics and summaries
.RE
.SS Performance
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
Parallel disk downloads
.IP \(bu 2
Resumable downloads with retry
.IP \(bu 2
Exponential backoff on errors
.IP \(bu 2
Streaming downloads (low memory usage)
.RE
.SS Safety
.RS 4
.IP \(bu 2
Read-only vSphere operations
.IP \(bu 2
Automatic cleanup on interrupt
.IP \(bu 2
Comprehensive error handling
.IP \(bu 2
Detailed logging
.RE
.SH KEYBOARD CONTROLS
In interactive mode:
.TP
.B Arrow Keys
Navigate VM list
.TP
.B Type
Filter/search VMs
.TP
.B Enter
Select VM and proceed
.TP
.B Ctrl+C
Cancel operation and exit
.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.SS Connection Errors
.PP
Verify credentials and network:
.RS 4
.nf
# Test URL
curl \-k $GOVC_URL

# Check firewall allows HTTPS (443)
telnet vcenter.example.com 443
.fi
.RE
.SS Slow Downloads
.PP
Increase worker count:
.RS 4
.nf
DOWNLOAD_WORKERS=8 hyperexport
.fi
.RE
.SS Certificate Errors
.PP
For self-signed certificates:
.RS 4
.nf
export GOVC_INSECURE=1
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/hypervisord/config.yaml
System-wide configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.hyperexport/config.yaml
User configuration file
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful export
.TP
.B 1
Connection or authentication error
.TP
.B 2
Export failed
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by user (Ctrl+C)
